<![endif]-->
<div id="architecture-and-design-team-27584" class="section section-scrollmation scrollmation-two-column section-two-column-27584 viewport-height-minheight" data-possible-scrollmation data-scrollmation-container="#architecture-and-design-team-27584">
  <div class="two-column-grid">
    <div class="column column-left main-column scrollmation-text">
      
        <div class="block heading-block"><h3>GREEN Architecture...</h3></div><div class="block scrollmation-image-block scrollmation-image-block-">
  <div class="inline-media">
    <div class="inline-image">
      <img src="./media/lpc-ventilation--heating-graphicbest_smallcomp-lr_2wkeeh9.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-ventilation--heating-graphicbest_smallcomp-mr_zkoaepz.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-ventilation--heating-graphicbest_smallcomp-lr_2wkeeh9.jpg" alt="Our plans were built around using as much natural light, heat and ventilation as possible" title="Our plans were built around using as much natural light, heat and ventilation as possible" />
    </div>
    
    <p class="scrollmation-image-block-caption caption">
      <p>Our plans were built around using as much natural light, heat and ventilation as possible</p>
    </p>
    
  </div>
</div><div class="block text-block"><p><strong>We had a clear aim for the Living Planet Centre from the start: to create an environmentally-sensitive building using responsibly-sourced materials.</strong>  </p>
<p>As well as meeting the general specifications and guidelines from bodies like the British Council for Offices – including adequate space for people to work, health and safety guidelines, etc – our building also had to meet our own high standards for low-carbon sustainability.  </p>
<p>A guiding principle from the start was <strong>passive design</strong> – incorporating elements like natural ventilation, effective insulation and low energy consumption. So the building itself would contribute to its own energy-efficiency and low-emissions operation.   </p></div><div class="block scrollmation-image-block scrollmation-image-block-">
  <div class="inline-media">
    <div class="inline-image">
      <img src="./media/hopkins-expanded-labelled-graphic_comp-lr_fdsqo7l.jpg" data-src755="./media/hopkins-expanded-labelled-graphic_comp-mr_xqmqpyu.jpg" data-src0="./media/hopkins-expanded-labelled-graphic_comp-lr_fdsqo7l.jpg" alt="Expanded graphic of Living Planet Centre design by Hopkins Architects" title="Expanded graphic of Living Planet Centre design by Hopkins Architects" />
    </div>
    
    <p class="scrollmation-image-block-caption caption">
      <p>Expanded graphic of Living Planet Centre design by Hopkins Architects</p>
    </p>
    
  </div>
</div><div class="block text-block"><p>An enormous amount of preparation work and research went into this whole project at every stage – including landscape and ecology surveys and detailed materials analysis. We wanted to make sure we’d create a building to be proud of – one that would meet the highest environmental and sustainability standards we could possibly achieve.   </p>
<p><strong>We set our sights on achieving an ‘Outstanding’ rating under the BREEAM environmental assessment scheme – which not many buildings in the UK had ever managed before.</strong>   </p></div><div class="block html-block"><div class="block text-block">
    <p class="custom-hide-link">
      Find out more about BREEAM
    </p>
    <span class="custom-hidden-text">
      <p><strong>BREEAM</strong>, the Building Research Establishment Environmental Assessment Method, is an assessment scheme for measuring impacts and sustainability of buildings, both in their construction and their day-to-day use.</p>

      <p>They take into consideration various scientifically-based environmental and social criteria – eg the building’s use of energy, water, land and materials, pollution and waste management, health and wellbeing, transport etc. An overall percentage score is calculated, which gives a BREEAM rating of either ‘Fail’, ‘Pass’, ‘Good’, ‘Very Good’, ‘Excellent’, or the notoriously hard-to-get ‘Outstanding’, which requires a score of 85% or more. Our Living Planet Centre went on to achieve a score of over 90%.</p>
    </span>
</div></div><div class="block text-block"></div><div class="block media-block media-block-video">
  <div class="inline-media">
    

    <div class="inline-video" data-video-player>
      <video class="video-js vjs-default-skin" width="100%" height="100%" preload="none" controls poster="./media/lpc_breeam_principles_vidstill_comp.jpg" alt="This short video explains more about the principles and process of BREEAM certification" aria-label="This short video explains more about the principles and process of BREEAM certification" ref="video" data-setup='{"controls":true,"autoplay":false,"preload":"none","width":"100%","height":"100%"}'>

          <source src="./media/breeam_video_compresed.mp4" type="video/mp4"/><source src="./media/video_file.webm" type="video/webm"/>
          <img src="./media/lpc_breeam_principles_vidstill_comp.jpg" title="Your browser does not support the <video> tag" alt="video fallback image"/>
      </video>
    </div>
    

      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        This short video explains more about the principles and process of BREEAM certification
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block scrollmation-image-block scrollmation-image-block-">
  <div class="inline-media">
    <div class="inline-image">
      <img src="./media/lpc_hopkins-two-tier-plan2_comp-lr_0emolea.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc_hopkins-two-tier-plan2_comp-mr_zstjjpx.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc_hopkins-two-tier-plan2_comp-lr_0emolea.jpg" alt="Plan of how the building&#x27;s two main levels would be used" title="Plan of how the building&#x27;s two main levels would be used" />
    </div>
    
    <p class="scrollmation-image-block-caption caption">
      <p>Plan of how the building's two main levels would be used</p>
    </p>
    
  </div>
</div><div class="block text-block"><p>We knew it wouldn’t be easy, but we were confident, enthusiastic and determined. And in the end, thanks to the great work of our partners on the project –particularly our architects <strong>Hopkins Architects</strong>, environmental designers <strong>Atelier Ten</strong> and builders <strong>Willmott Dixon</strong> – we achieved our aims and more.  </p></div><div class="block scrollmation-image-block scrollmation-image-block-">
  <div class="inline-media">
    <div class="inline-image">
      <img src="./media/lpc-landscape-context_crop-hopkins_comp-lr_xewerby.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-landscape-context_crop-hopkins_comp-mr_uiz58bj.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-landscape-context_crop-hopkins_comp-lr_xewerby.jpg" alt="Our plans also took into account the local ecology of the area" title="Our plans also took into account the local ecology of the area" />
    </div>
    
    <p class="scrollmation-image-block-caption caption">
      <p>Our plans also took into account the local ecology of the area</p>
    </p>
    
  </div>
</div><figure class="block quote-block">
  <blockquote>
<p>“We are very excited… We want it to be a pioneering sustainable project.”  </p>
</blockquote>
    <figcaption class="quote-cite">Mike Taylor, Hopkins Architects</figcaption>
  
</figure><div class="block text-block"></div><figure class="block quote-block">
  <blockquote>
<p>“It’s a testbed for so many technologies and ideas, all brought together to make a holistic, new type of building.”  </p>
</blockquote>
    <figcaption class="quote-cite">Patrick Bellew, Atelier Ten</figcaption>
  
</figure><div class="block scrollmation-image-block scrollmation-image-block-">
  <div class="inline-media">
    <div class="inline-image">
      <img src="./media/lpc_atelier-ten-facade-louvres-graphic_comp-lr_nyxbwu8.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc_atelier-ten-facade-louvres-graphic_comp-mr_s2eplgh.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc_atelier-ten-facade-louvres-graphic_comp-lr_nyxbwu8.jpg" alt="One of Atelier Ten&#x27;s many contributions was working out how to shade the building from the sun at different times and seasons" title="One of Atelier Ten&#x27;s many contributions was working out how to shade the building from the sun at different times and seasons" />
    </div>
    
    <p class="scrollmation-image-block-caption caption">
      <p>One of Atelier Ten's many contributions was working out how to shade the building from the sun at different times and seasons</p>
    </p>
    
  </div>
</div><figure class="block quote-block">
  <blockquote>
<p>“(WWF) are just so forward-thinking with this building... it’s refreshing in the construction industry.”  </p>
</blockquote>
    <figcaption class="quote-cite">Richard Bartlett, Willmott Dixon</figcaption>
  
</figure><div class="block text-block"></div><figure class="block quote-block">
  <blockquote>
<p>“Hopkins’ trademark preoccupation with structural expressionism and modular components is on full display here but it is delivered in a sensitive manner that is sympathetic to the tactile, naturalistic intimacy requested by their client.”  </p>
</blockquote>
    <figcaption class="quote-cite">Thomas Lane, 'Building' magazine</figcaption>
  
</figure><div class="block text-block"></div><div class="block heading-block"><h3>MEET THE TEAM...</h3></div><div class="block text-block"><p><strong>The main people working most closely with us as partners on the design, planning and construction were:</strong>  </p>
<p>•    <strong>The architects – Hopkins Architects:</strong> planned the whole original concept, look and layout, exterior and interior design, and so much more.  </p>
<p>•    <strong>The environmental design consultants/engineers – Atelier Ten:</strong> provided indispensable insights on sustainable design aspects of the building, including energy and thermal modelling, daylight/artificial light analysis and more.  </p></div><div class="block scrollmation-image-block scrollmation-image-block-">
  <div class="inline-media">
    <div class="inline-image">
      <img src="./media/hopkins-tree-survey-whole_comp-lr_dwdbs8g.jpg" data-src755="./media/hopkins-tree-survey-whole_comp-mr_5abmycb.jpg" data-src0="./media/hopkins-tree-survey-whole_comp-lr_dwdbs8g.jpg" alt="The landscaping plans included incorporating as many of the existing trees as possible, and replanting others" title="The landscaping plans included incorporating as many of the existing trees as possible, and replanting others" />
    </div>
    
    <p class="scrollmation-image-block-caption caption">
      <p>The landscaping plans included incorporating as many of the existing trees as possible, and replanting others</p>
    </p>
    
  </div>
</div><div class="block text-block"><p>•    <strong>The main contractor/builder – Willmott Dixon:</strong> led the project from the construction stage (more of which in a minute). They were hired on a ‘design and build’ contract, which meant they’d oversee all elements of the planning and construction, working alongside Hopkins, Atelier Ten and the many subcontractors involved. Together they made sure we achieved the required BREEAM Outstanding rating for the Living Planet Centre.  </p>
<p>•    <strong>The structural design/civil engineers – Expedition Engineering:</strong> advised on and checked the strength, stability and sustainability of the various elements of the design and construction, and much more.   </p>
<p>•    <strong>The carbon emissions consultants – Sturgis Carbon Profiling:</strong> looked at every process and material proposed by the architects, designers and builders and suggested ways of reducing carbon emissions without going over-budget.   </p></div><div class="block scrollmation-image-block scrollmation-image-block-">
  <div class="inline-media">
    <div class="inline-image">
      <img src="./media/grant-ass_outside-with-plants_comp-lr_y22wucu.jpg" data-src755="./media/grant-ass_outside-with-plants_comp-mr_wcfyiuf.jpg" data-src0="./media/grant-ass_outside-with-plants_comp-lr_y22wucu.jpg" alt="Grant Associates, the landscape architects, also helped us consider what would be seen from inside and outside the building" title="Grant Associates, the landscape architects, also helped us consider what would be seen from inside and outside the building" />
    </div>
    
    <p class="scrollmation-image-block-caption caption">
      <p>Grant Associates, the landscape architects, also helped us consider what would be seen from inside and outside the building</p>
    </p>
    
  </div>
</div><div class="block text-block"><p>•    <strong>The landscape architects – Grant Associates:</strong> helped make sure the building blended into its environment in an ecologically sensitive, integrated and sustainable way.  </p>
<p>•    <strong>The office space planners – AMA Alexi Marmot Associates:</strong> their analysis helped us work out the best way to make use of our working space.  </p>
<p>•    <strong>The project managers/property consultants – King Sturge and Doherty Baines:</strong> helped coordinate everyone and helped keep the project on schedule and on budget.  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-video">
  <div class="inline-media">
    

    <div class="inline-video" data-video-player>
