<div id="wwf-experience-67313" class="section section-text-over-media section-text-over-image section-text-over-media-67313 has-text viewport-height">
  <div class="text text-over-media-inner right center large">
    
      <h2 class="text-inner">
        WWF experience
      </h2>
    
  </div>

  <div class="background-overlay"></div>

  
    <p class="caption text-over-media-caption main-text-is-center"><strong>Join us for a look around the Jason Bruges Studio-designed visitor zones at the Living Planet Centre...</strong></p>
  

  <div class="section-background section-background-fixed">
    
      <picture class="section-background-image text-over-media-background-image">
        <source 
            srcset="./media/lpc-visitor-experience038_largecomp2-lr.jpg 1001w,
                ./media/lpc-visitor-experience038_largecomp2-mr.jpg 1401w,
                ./media/lpc-visitor-experience038_largecomp2-hr.jpg">

        

        <img src="./media/lpc-visitor-experience038_largecomp2-mr.jpg" data-object-fit="cover" data-autoscale-content-ratio="1.48698884758">
      </picture>
    
  </div>
</div>

<!--[if IE 9]>
<script>
  (function() {
    // IE9 fix to stop audio playing
    var video = document.getElementById('video-wwf-experience-67313');
    if (video){
      video.muted = true;
    }
  })();
</script>
<![endif]-->
<div id="scrollmation-background-33543" class="section section-scrollmation scrollmation-background section-scrollmation-33543 inner-column-right" data-scrollmation-container=".section-scrollmation-33543" data-scrollmation="background" data-viewport-height data-viewport-height-property="min-height">
  
    <div class="tiny-scrollmation" data-viewport-height data-viewport-height-scale="0.66"></div>
    <style>
      .section-scrollmation-33543 .tiny-scrollmation {
        background-image: url(./media/wwfexperience_inside_tg14222_largecomp3-lr_zjmzlq8.jpg);
        background-position: top left;
      }
    </style>
  

  <div class="two-column-grid">
    <div class="column column-right main-column scrollmation-text">
      <div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc-visitor-experience_high_smallcomp-lr_qy5slfw.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-visitor-experience_high_smallcomp-mr_hktnxwv.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-visitor-experience_high_smallcomp-lr_qy5slfw.jpg" alt="For the first time at WWF-UK we&amp;#39;ve opened our doors to the public – welcome to the WWF Experience!" title="For the first time at WWF-UK we&amp;#39;ve opened our doors to the public – welcome to the WWF Experience!" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>For the first time at WWF-UK we've opened our doors to the public – welcome to the WWF Experience!</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>We always knew we’d have some kind of ‘visitor facility’ or public exhibition area in the Living Planet Centre – it was a key requirement of the original Rufford Foundation funding. But we just weren’t sure at first what form it should take.</strong>  </p>
<p><strong>It’s not something we’d ever done before. Our old Panda House building was particularly ill-equipped (and not especially appealing) for visitors.</strong>   </p>
<p><strong>So there were lots of differing opinions about what our new visitor experience should be like, and the logistics of how we’d run it.</strong>   </p>
<p><strong>For instance, who should the target audience be, should it be open every day, should we charge for admission, and so on.</strong>  </p>
<p><strong>In the end we opted for a free public exhibition, ambitiously covering all the main strands of our global work and aimed at a wide audience – primarily with families and schoolchildren in mind.</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/wwf-experience-inside-zone-father-child_comp-lr_rzhjub8.jpg" data-src755="./media/wwf-experience-inside-zone-father-child_comp-mr_8nfzlkb.jpg" data-src0="./media/wwf-experience-inside-zone-father-child_comp-lr_rzhjub8.jpg" alt="Families and children are particularly encouraged to come and enjoy the WWF Experience" title="Families and children are particularly encouraged to come and enjoy the WWF Experience" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Families and children are particularly encouraged to come and enjoy the WWF Experience</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>We have lots of fascinating information to offer – wild facts, stories and images – but we needed an eye-catching and memorable showcase to present our work.</strong>   </p>
<p><strong>That’s where Jason Bruges Studio came in...</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/jason-bruges-in-lpc-experience-smallcomp-lr_p26lfvj.jpg" data-src755="./media/jason-bruges-in-lpc-experience-smallcomp-mr_p6jnpv1.jpg" data-src0="./media/jason-bruges-in-lpc-experience-smallcomp-lr_p26lfvj.jpg" alt="Designer Jason Bruges inside one of the four WWF Experience zones that he and his studio created for the Living Planet Centre" title="Designer Jason Bruges inside one of the four WWF Experience zones that he and his studio created for the Living Planet Centre" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Designer Jason Bruges inside one of the four WWF Experience zones that he and his studio created for the Living Planet Centre</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block html-block"><div class="block text-block">
  <p>
    <strong>‘Jason Bruges Studio had already been involved with WWF when they contributed to our <span class="custom-hide-link">Pandamonium’ fundraising art exhibition in 2009,</span> restyling old panda coin-collecting boxes in an unexpected and creative way.</strong>
  </p>
  <span class="custom-hidden-text">
    <div class="block media-block media-block-youtube">
      <div class="inline-media">
        <div class="inline-youtube">
          <iframe id="scrollmation-background-33543-block-7" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/WCce646GqIE?enablejsapi=1&amp;rel=0" frameborder="0" width="560" height="315" allowfullscreen=""></iframe>
        </div>
          <p class="media-block-caption caption">
            <b>Jason Bruges Studio's fascinating, if slightly unnerving, 'Panda Eyes' artwork – created for our 2009 Pandamonium exhibition, and now on display in the Living Planet Centre&nbsp;</b>
          </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Jason Bruges Studio's ‘Panda Eyes’ exhibit – with 100 mini pandas revolving to follow visitor movements – now takes pride of place in our gallery space on the entrance level, having been kindly donated to us by our former chairman Ed Smith.</strong></p>
  </span>
</div></div><div class="block text-block"><p><strong>We commissioned Jason Bruges Studio to design and build four ‘zone’ structures for the WWF Experience in the entrance area of the Living Planet Centre.</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc-experience_zone-model_comp-lr_jhjphhb.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-experience_zone-model_comp-mr_yb5wc5v.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-experience_zone-model_comp-lr_jhjphhb.jpg" alt="Early carved-wood scale model of the flowerpot-shaped zones designed by Jason Bruges Studio" title="Early carved-wood scale model of the flowerpot-shaped zones designed by Jason Bruges Studio" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        Early carved-wood scale model of the flowerpot-shaped zones designed by Jason Bruges Studio
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>Each of the four zones reflects a different environmental theme, and key area of WWF’s work</strong> <strong>–</strong> <strong>namely:</strong>  </p>
<p><strong>WILDLIFE zone – catch glimpses and fascinating facts about rare species...</strong>  </p>
<p><strong>FORESTS zone – experience the sights and sounds of a day in a rainforest...</strong>  </p>
<p><strong>RIVERS zone – follow the flow of a river from source to estuary...</strong>  </p>
<p><strong>OCEANS zone – see the amazing variety of creatures and plants at sea...</strong>   </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc-visitor-experience-zones_smallcomp2-lr_x3lurq6.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-visitor-experience-zones_smallcomp2-mr_iojkems.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-visitor-experience-zones_smallcomp2-lr_x3lurq6.jpg" alt="Our four Visitor Experience zones are just inside the entrance to the Living Planet Centre" title="Our four Visitor Experience zones are just inside the entrance to the Living Planet Centre" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Our four Visitor Experience zones are just inside the entrance to the Living Planet Centre</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>The four cone-shaped constructions, with their slatted timber ‘fins’ neatly echoing the louvred facade outside the building, were designed to be immersive, interactive ‘sensory feasts’ for visitors of all ages.</strong>   </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/wwf-experience-w-wheelchair-users_comp-lr_7gkxzsj.jpg" data-src755="./media/wwf-experience-w-wheelchair-users_comp-mr_3n3yka1.jpg" data-src0="./media/wwf-experience-w-wheelchair-users_comp-lr_7gkxzsj.jpg" alt="Our visitor experience is wheelchair-friendly and suitable for all age groups" title="Our visitor experience is wheelchair-friendly and suitable for all age groups" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Our visitor experience is wheelchair-friendly and suitable for all age groups</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>All four zones are accesible for wheelchair-users. Low-height entrances are also included to encourage children to crawl through and explore. The timber frames, all sustainably sourced, are designed to be touched.</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/wwf-experience-w-children3_comptristanfewingswwf-lr_d8io0m0.jpg" data-src755="./media/wwf-experience-w-children3_comptristanfewingswwf-mr_8o0f6d6.jpg" data-src0="./media/wwf-experience-w-children3_comptristanfewingswwf-lr_d8io0m0.jpg" alt="Lots for young ones to do, see and learn..." title="Lots for young ones to do, see and learn..." />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Lots for young ones to do, see and learn...</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>The zones reflect the sights, sounds and ambience of the particular environments.</strong>   </p>
<p><strong>As visitors enter each zone, low-energy video screens begin running footage of the natural world, which was developed in conjunction with the BBC and other partners.</strong>   </p>
<p><strong>Bronze casts, based on real natural features, also help people interact with each environment.</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc_lioness_bronze_amasters_comp-lr.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc_lioness_bronze_amasters_comp-mr.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc_lioness_bronze_amasters_comp-lr.jpg" alt="Lioness paw in bronze – one of André Masters&amp;#39; tactile animal casts" title="Lioness paw in bronze – one of André Masters&amp;#39; tactile animal casts" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Lioness paw in bronze – one of André Masters' tactile animal casts</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>We commissioned sculptor André Masters to create seven unique bronze casts based on rare or endangered species – including lion, tiger and monkey paws, a sea turtle flipper and a conch shell.</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc_sea-turtle_bronze_amasters_comp-lr_a5lcrs2.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc_sea-turtle_bronze_amasters_comp-mr_fn3vqwq.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc_sea-turtle_bronze_amasters_comp-lr_a5lcrs2.jpg" alt="Sea turtle flipper – another of André Master&amp;#39;s wildlife-themed bronze casts" title="Sea turtle flipper – another of André Master&amp;#39;s wildlife-themed bronze casts" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Sea turtle flipper – another of André Master's wildlife-themed bronze casts</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/wwf-experience-inside-oceans-zone_comp-lr_2fxcdkc.jpg" data-src755="./media/wwf-experience-inside-oceans-zone_comp-mr_ari323f.jpg" data-src0="./media/wwf-experience-inside-oceans-zone_comp-lr_2fxcdkc.jpg" alt="Inside the Oceans zone at the WWF Experience" title="Inside the Oceans zone at the WWF Experience" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Inside the Oceans zone at the WWF Experience</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>Each zone also has its own specially-written soundtrack created by acclaimed composer William Goodchild. They're all distinctive but subtly complement each other.</strong>   </p>
<p><strong>The soundtracks and background noises are also triggered when visitors enter the zone, and are played through hidden ‘feonic’ speakers.</strong>   </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/wwf-experience-zone-from-above_comp-lr_08cr6rw.jpg" data-src755="./media/wwf-experience-zone-from-above_comp-mr_0z0sv4u.jpg" data-src0="./media/wwf-experience-zone-from-above_comp-lr_08cr6rw.jpg" alt="" title="" />
      
    </div>
    

  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>This efficient audio technology effectively turns the whole wooden structure of the zone into a giant speaker, producing an enveloping but focused sound that doesn’t travel too far into the rest of the building.</strong>  </p>
<p><strong>Concealed low-energy LEDs provide mood-lighting effects to accompany the video and audio.</strong>   </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/wwfexperience_zones2_compjennipystynen-lr_wttexga.jpg" data-src755="./media/wwfexperience_zones2_compjennipystynen-mr_fomfgbd.jpg" data-src0="./media/wwfexperience_zones2_compjennipystynen-lr_wttexga.jpg" alt="" title="" />
      
    </div>
    

  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>Relevant and thought-provoking quotes inspired by the themes of each zone are etched into the wooden fins inside the structures.</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc-experience-w-quote_comp-lr_fw9sbmk.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-experience-w-quote_comp-mr_uoutvps.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-experience-w-quote_comp-lr_fw9sbmk.jpg" alt="" title="" />
      
    </div>
    

  </div>
</div>
<div class="block media-block media-block-youtube">
  <div class="inline-media">
    
    <div class="inline-youtube">
      <iframe id="scrollmation-background-33543-block-26" src="//www.youtube.com/embed/inJ5XaZaoTk?enablejsapi=1&rel=0" frameborder="0" width="560" height="315" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    </div>
    


      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>A quick 30-second video tour of the WWF Experience</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong>All visitors to the WWF Experience, adults and children alike, are also encouraged to take part in quizzes, 'treasure hunts' and other interactive games designed to educate and inspire.</strong>  </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc-experience-w-quiz_comp-lr_1aqbb9b.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-experience-w-quiz_comp-mr_is8bsxv.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-experience-w-quiz_comp-lr_1aqbb9b.jpg" alt="Doing one of our quizzes..." title="Doing one of our quizzes..." />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Doing one of our quizzes...</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block text-block"><p><strong><a href="http://www.wwf.org.uk/livingplanetcentrestory/#life-at-the-living-planet-centre-67317" target="_blank">&gt; Find out more about the day-to-day use of the Living Planet Centre.</a></strong>   </p></div><div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/inside-forests-zone-pod_smallcomp-lr_adpey0n.jpg" data-src755="./media/inside-forests-zone-pod_smallcomp-mr_pbmsdhf.jpg" data-src0="./media/inside-forests-zone-pod_smallcomp-lr_adpey0n.jpg" alt="Inside the Forests zone at the WWF Experience" title="Inside the Forests zone at the WWF Experience" />
      
    </div>
    
      <p class="media-block-caption caption">
        <b>Inside the Forests zone at the WWF Experience</b>
      </p>
    
  </div>
</div>
<div class="block media-block media-block-image">
  <div class="inline-media">
    


    <div class="inline-image">
      
      <img src="./media/lpc-visitor-experience015_smallcomp2-lr.jpg" data-src755="./media/lpc-visitor-experience015_smallcomp2-mr.jpg" data-src0="./media/lpc-visitor-experience015_smallcomp2-lr.jpg" alt="Inside the Rivers zone" title="Inside the Rivers zone" />
      
